import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
newarray=pd.read_csv('~/Downloads/titanic-passengers.csv',sep=';')
newarray['Age'].fillna(newarray['Age'].mean(),inplace=True)
newarray.drop('Cabin',axis='columns',inplace=True)
newarray.isnull().sum()
newarray
print(newarray['Embarked'].value_counts())
newarray['Embarked'].fillna('S',inplace=True)
surv={'Survived':{'No':0,'Yes':1}}
newarray.replace(surv,inplace=True)
sexs={'Sex':{'male':0,'female':1}}
newarray.replace(sexs,inplace=True)

def plot_correlation_map( df ):

    corr = df.corr()

    s , ax = plt.subplots( figsize =( 12 , 10 ) )

    cmap = sns.diverging_palette( 220 , 10 , as_cmap = True )

    s = sns.heatmap(

        corr, 

        cmap = cmap,

        square=True, 

        cbar_kws={ 'shrink' : .9 }, 

        ax=ax, 

        annot = True, 

        annot_kws = { 'fontsize' : 12 }

        )
